Fever Reporter KOKSTAD SAPS have confirmed a case of culpable homicide after a 62-year-old woman died when she was knocked down by a truck last Friday, November 9. The woman was going to work when the accident occurred between Hope Street and Zietsman Street at 7 am. SAPS spokesperson Captain Dumisani Ncongo said the woman died on the scene. “I was on my way to work when I saw the accident. The woman was about to cross the road when she was hit by the truck,” said a local man who witnessed the accident, saying it has left him traumatised.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.